The paper deals with object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The analysis of errors in object detectors and the study of invariance properties of models are also related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of benchmarks and datasets is also relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
